Here is the cleaned up text:

Accurately Derive Prices from Products and Assets Using Salesforce...
Automatically Populate Output Variables for Pricing Elements
Easily Update Context Tags
Enhance Pricing Data Security
Tailor Pricing Discounts for Your Business Using Contract-Based...
Track Pricing Data Using Event Log Files
Monitor Your Pricing Data From the Operations Console
Comprehensively Track Product Cost by Using Cost Books
Search for Any Price Book with the Redesigned Price Book Component

Calculate accurate prices for all your line items by deriving a productâ€™s price from other source products or assets. Set profile-level security for each element within a pricing procedure. Use the Operations Console to see all your pricing data. Dynamically map output variables in a lookup table and change context tag values for variables.

Create derived price records to determine a product's price by using another pricing source, such as a product or an asset. Incorporate a wide range of pricing factors and enhance pricing accuracy and accurate pricing for your derived products.

Set default mappings for specific output columns of lookup tables associated with the List Price and Price Adjustment Matrix elements to reduce manual user entry.

Use the Assignment element in a pricing procedure to set and change the context tag values of variables. Give users flexibility to customise a variable's value within a pricing procedure and enable their business to optimise their pricing strategies for maximum effectiveness.

Set profile-level access to grant access to all pricing elements in a pricing procedure. Based on the security level you set, only the users who have access can see pricing information.

Implement contract-based pricing to set discounts to specific business conditions using predefined Contract Pricing Entries lookup table. Establish pricing rules linked to contracts and turn on the contract-based pricing option in a pricing element.

To get a complete overview of your pricing procedures being executed, use the new Pricing events. Use the Pricing event log file type to measure how long it takes to run the pricing APIs.

Get a complete overview of the pricing data from the Operations Console. At a glance, you see the data consumed when pricing operations are performed and the event log files generated during the execution of pricing processes.

Create and organize multiple cost books to define expenses that occur when you create a product. Set a default cost book and create individual cost book entries to track all the cost factors associated with product creation.

The modification of Lightning components, Salesforce Lightning Design System (SLDS) styles, and custom properties help users use the new record pickers to search for any price book.
